    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-18T06:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-18T06:44:00-05:00" n="302"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-18T11:00:00-00:44"
                            >June 18, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Mass meeting was held yesterday by ex-President Howard, Chief Justice
                    Johnson, Gray,<note n="27" xml:id="d302fn27">P. O. Gray, editor of the <hi
                            rend="italic">Liberia Express and Agricultural World</hi>.</note> and
                    Faulkner and adopted resolutions condemning the present administration for its
                    part in the slave trade and further that the people of Liberia desired the
                    officials responsible removed from office.</p>
                <p>[Paraphrase.] In spite of the Liberian Government’s determined opposition, the
                    meeting was held and there were about 200 persons in attendance. While it is
                    doubted that this meeting will have any direct effect, it does show the general
                    feeling of a large portion of the population. Despatch follows by pouch.<note
                        n="28" xml:id="d302fn28">Not printed.</note> [End paraphrase.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
